---
import Base, { BOOKING_URL } from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Chris Colborne - Custom Web Apps, Dashboards & AI Tools | Brisbane"
  description="I build custom software for businesses that have outgrown spreadsheets and off-the-shelf tools. Web apps, dashboards, AI-powered automation. Book a free call."
>
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="eyebrow">G'day, I'm Chris 👋</p>
        <h1>
          I build <span class="thing"><span class="word" id="rotator">your thing</span></span>.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede">
          The custom web app you've been meaning to get built. The dashboard that pulls your data
          into one place. The AI tool that does the boring bit for you. Designed around how your
          business actually works - not how some off-the-shelf product thinks it should.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-big" href={BOOKING_URL}>Book a free call</a>
        <p class="small">Software engineer, 15+ years shipping. Based in Brisbane, work with anyone.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band" id="services">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">What I build</p>
        <h2>Software that fits your business</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Custom web apps</h3>
            <p>
              The workflow that currently lives in three spreadsheets and one person's head, turned
              into something your whole team can use.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Dashboards &amp; data tools</h3>
            <p>
              Your numbers, live, in one place - instead of exported, emailed, and out of date by
              Tuesday.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>AI-powered tools</h3>
            <p>
              Automation for the repetitive stuff: document processing, data extraction, drafting,
              categorising. The tasks nobody wants and everybody has.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band" id="work">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">Recent work</p>
        <h2>Built and shipped</h2>
        <div class="work-item">
          <span class="tag">Legal · Practice management</span>
          <h3>Practice management software for a law firm</h3>
          <p>
            A custom system handling matters, documents, and workflow for a legal practice -
            replacing a patchwork of tools with one that fits how they run.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <span class="tag">Energy · Notifications</span>
          <h3>Scheduled outage alerts</h3>
          <p>
            A system that tracked planned power outages, pinpointed the businesses in each affected
            area using mapping and location data, and gave them a heads-up before the lights went
            out - turning a disruptive surprise into a manageable one.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <span class="tag">Data · Consumer</span>
          <h3>Fuel Tracker</h3>
          <p>
            A live fuel-price tracker for Queensland drivers, collecting and serving price data
            around the clock. Built end-to-end: data pipeline, API, and app.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band" id="how">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">How it works</p>
        <h2>Three steps, no drama</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="num">1</div>
            <h3>We talk.</h3>
            <p>
              A free 30-minute call. You tell me the problem in plain English - no spec document
              required. If I'm not the right fit, I'll tell you that too.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="num">2</div>
            <h3>I build.</h3>
            <p>
              Clear scope, clear price, regular demos as it comes together. You'll never wonder
              what's happening.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="num">3</div>
            <h3>You own it.</h3>
            <p>
              Your software, your code, your data. No lock-in, no ransom, no "per-seat pricing
              surprise" two years in.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band" id="about">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">About</p>
        <div class="about">
          <img src="/profile-pic.jpg" alt="Chris Colborne" width="150" height="150" />
          <div>
            <h2>The person behind the keyboard</h2>
            <p>
              I'm an Aussie software engineer from Brisbane with over 15 years of experience
              building software - from scrappy internal tools to systems used by millions. By day I
              build video and AI tooling at Microsoft. On the side, I help small
              businesses get software that actually fits.
            </p>
            <p>
              I've been writing about software since 2015 - you can dig through the archive on the <a href="/blog/">blog</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band faq" id="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">FAQ</p>
        <h2>The questions everyone asks</h2>
        <details>
          <summary>What does it cost?</summary>
          <p>
            Depends on the thing. Small tools start in the low thousands; bigger builds are scoped
            and priced up front so there are no surprises. The call is free either way.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How long does it take?</summary>
          <p>
            Most projects ship a first working version in 2–6 weeks. You'll see progress from week
            one.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What if I don't know exactly what I need?</summary>
          <p>
            That's normal - most people don't. Describing the problem is enough; figuring out the
            right shape of the solution is part of what you're paying me for.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Who owns the result?</summary>
          <p>You do. Code, data, accounts - all yours.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-final">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>Got a thing that needs building?</h2>
        <p>
          Thirty minutes, no obligation, no jargon. Worst case, you leave with a clearer idea of
          what you need.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-big" href={BOOKING_URL}>Book a free call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    // Rotate the "thing" - the one moment of motion on the page.
    const words = ['your thing', 'your web app', 'your dashboard', 'your AI tool'];
    const el = document.getElementById('rotator');
    const reduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
    if (el && !reduced) {
      let i = 0;
      setInterval(() => {
        el.classList.add('swap-out');
        setTimeout(() => {
          i = (i + 1) % words.length;
          el.textContent = words[i];
          el.classList.remove('swap-out');
          el.classList.add('swap-in');
          setTimeout(() => el.classList.remove('swap-in'), 260);
        }, 200);
      }, 2600);
    }
  </script>
</Base>
